===Etymology===
* First attested in the 1620s.
* {{sense|award|praise}} First attested in 1852.
* {{borrowed}} {{etyl|fr|en}}, from {{etyl|oc|en}} {{term|acolada||an embrace|lang=oc}}, from {{etyl|oc|en}} {{term|acolar||an embrace|lang=oc}}, from {{etyl|it|en}} {{term|accolata|lang=it}}, from {{etyl|VL.|en}} {{term|accolare|accolāre|to hug around the neck|lang=it}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|ad-|lang=la}} + {{term|collum||neck|lang=la}} (English {{term|collar|lang=en}}).

===Pronunciation===
